# Hard tier tasks — 10 tasks
# Format: task_name|prompt

concurrent-trie|Work in /tmp/training-trie/. Init go mod (go mod init training/trie). Implement a concurrent trie in trie.go (package main) with Insert(word string), Search(word string) bool, Delete(word string) bool — safe for concurrent use with sync.RWMutex. Write trie_test.go with sequential tests AND a concurrent stress test using t.Parallel() and 20 goroutines each doing 100 Insert/Search/Delete ops. Include a benchmark BenchmarkConcurrentInsert. Run go test -race -bench=. ./... and report full output. Acceptance: race detector clean, all tests pass.
event-bus|Work in /tmp/training-eventbus/. Init go mod (go mod init training/eventbus). Implement EventBus in bus.go (package main): Subscribe(topic string) <-chan string, Publish(topic string, msg string), Unsubscribe(topic string, ch <-chan string), support wildcard topics using * suffix (e.g. "user.*" matches "user.created"). All ops thread-safe. Write bus_test.go with tests for basic pub/sub, wildcard matching, unsubscribe, and a concurrent test with 5 publishers and 10 subscribers. Run go test -race ./... Acceptance: race clean, wildcards work, no deadlock.
circuit-breaker|Work in /tmp/training-cb/. Init go mod (go mod init training/cb). Implement CircuitBreaker in cb.go (package main) with states Closed/Open/HalfOpen, configurable FailureThreshold int, SuccessThreshold int, Timeout time.Duration. Method Execute(fn func() error) error returns ErrCircuitOpen when open. Transitions: Closed to Open after N failures; Open to HalfOpen after Timeout; HalfOpen to Closed after M successes. Write cb_test.go with tests for each state transition and concurrent Execute calls. Run go test -race ./... Acceptance: all state transitions correct, race clean.
bimap|Work in /tmp/training-bimap/. Init go mod (go mod init training/bimap). Implement generic BiMap[K comparable, V comparable] in bimap.go (package main): Put(k K, v V), GetByKey(k K) (V, bool), GetByValue(v V) (K, bool), DeleteByKey(k K), DeleteByValue(v V), Len() int. All ops O(1) via two internal maps. Write bimap_test.go with tests for int-string and string-string, including duplicate key/value collision behavior. Run go test ./... Acceptance: all tests pass.
sieve-optimized|Work in /tmp/training-sieve/. Init go mod (go mod init training/sieve). Implement optimized Sieve of Eratosthenes in sieve.go (package main): Primes(n int) []int returns all primes <= n. Use a bitset ([]uint64) instead of []bool to reduce memory 8x. Skip even numbers. Write sieve_test.go verifying primes up to 100, 1000, 1000000 (count=78498). Add BenchmarkSieve running Primes(10_000_000). Run go test -bench=. ./... Acceptance: correct counts, benchmark completes.
lfu-cache|Work in /tmp/training-lfu/. Init go mod (go mod init training/lfu). Implement thread-safe LFU (Least Frequently Used) cache in lfu.go (package main): NewLFU(capacity int) *LFU, Get(key int) (int, bool), Put(key int, value int). O(1) Get and Put using a frequency doubly-linked list. On tie in frequency evict least recently used. Write lfu_test.go with tests for capacity 1, 2, eviction order, and a concurrent test. Run go test -race ./... Acceptance: O(1) ops, correct eviction, race clean.
rope-string|Work in /tmp/training-rope/. Init go mod (go mod init training/rope). Implement a Rope data structure in rope.go (package main) for efficient string manipulation: NewRope(s string) *Rope, Index(i int) byte, Concat(other *Rope) *Rope, Split(i int) (*Rope, *Rope), String() string. Internal nodes store weight (left subtree byte count). Write rope_test.go testing Index, Concat, Split on strings up to 10000 chars. Verify Split+Concat round-trips. Run go test ./... Acceptance: all tests pass.
merkle-tree|Work in /tmp/training-merkle/. Init go mod (go mod init training/merkle). Implement Merkle tree in merkle.go (package main): Build(data [][]byte) *MerkleTree using SHA-256 for leaves and internal nodes, Root() []byte, Proof(index int) [][]byte, Verify(leaf []byte, proof [][]byte, root []byte) bool. Write merkle_test.go with 1/2/4/7 leaf tests, proof generation and verification. Introduce tampered leaf and verify Verify returns false. Run go test ./... Acceptance: all tests pass, tampered data rejected.
skiplist|Work in /tmp/training-skiplist/. Init go mod (go mod init training/skiplist). Implement concurrent skip list in skiplist.go (package main): NewSkipList() *SkipList, Insert(key int, value any), Search(key int) (any, bool), Delete(key int) bool, Range(lo, hi int) []int. Use per-level mutexes. Max level 32, p=0.5. Write skiplist_test.go with sequential correctness tests AND concurrent test: 8 goroutines each inserting 1000 unique keys, then verify all 8000 keys searchable. Run go test -race ./... Acceptance: race clean, all keys found.
bounded-chan|Work in /tmp/training-bchan/. Init go mod (go mod init training/bchan). Implement generic bounded blocking channel BoundedChan[T any] in chan.go: New(capacity int) *BoundedChan[T], Send(ctx context.Context, v T) error, Recv(ctx context.Context) (T, error), Len() int, Cap() int. Send blocks when full respecting ctx cancellation. Write chan_test.go with producer-consumer test 10 goroutines each side, and context cancellation test. Run go test -race ./... Acceptance: no deadlock, race clean, cancellation works.
